benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/overdue - Retrieve overdue state for account

covered: GET Method - Valid Request: TC01 and TC02 cover successful retrieval scenarios for valid account and for account with no overdue
Authorization: TC07 and TC08 cover missing/invalid token cases
Not Found / Empty Dataset: TC03 (non-existent account) and TC13 (empty database) cover 404 responses
Input Validation & Security: TC04, TC05, TC06, TC10, TC11, TC16 validate malformed/missing/invalid accountId patterns and injection/XSS attempts
Error Handling: TC09 (500) and TC17 (503/504 dependency degraded) cover server-side failures
Query Parameters: TC12 verifies extra query parameters are ignored
Performance: TC14 (response time) and TC15 (concurrent requests) cover performance expectations
Resilience: TC19 covers retry behavior on transient network failures
Payload & Compatibility: TC18 ensures large payload handling; TC20 covers backward compatibility of response structure
gaps: Pagination: no tests for paginating through multiple overdue records
Caching Behavior: no tests asserting ETag/Cache-Control headers
Rate Limiting: no tests for throttling or 429 responses
Authorization edge case: no test for 403 when token has insufficient privileges
Error payload validation: no explicit checks on error payload structure beyond a generic message
Additional edge cases: more URL-encoded or mixed-encoding accountId handling not covered
recommendations: Add pagination tests for endpoints that return lists to verify correct handling of page size, page tokens, and total counts.
Add caching tests to validate ETag and Cache-Control headers and cache validation behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify proper handling under burst traffic (expect 429 or throttling).
Add explicit 403 tests for insufficient privileges in authenticated scenarios.
Enhance error payload checks to validate schema: error code, message, and details fields.
Test with more encoded input (percent-encoding), URL-unsafe characters, and boundary cases not just spaces or semicolons.
Strengthen security tests with broader injection vectors and proper sanitization checks.
Explicitly document and test retry/backoff semantics for transient network failures (TC19) including max retries.
